      "content": "A high-pitched squeal when braking, especially on the passenger side, is quite a concerning symptom. It's possible that your Camry's brake pads are worn down, causing the metal on the rotor to vibrate and produce the squeal. You might also want to inspect the brake pads and rotors for excessive wear or damage. It's a good idea to have a mechanic take a closer look to determine the root cause. \n\nIn the meantime, you can try to minimize the squealing by applying gentle, gradual pressure to the brake pedal when slowing down. This might help reduce the stress on the brake system. \n\nIt's also worth noting that worn-out brake pads can be a bit tricky to diagnose, especially if you're not familiar with the mechanics of your vehicle. It's a good idea to consult a professional mechanic to get a proper diagnosis and recommend the necessary repairs. \n\nYou might also consider getting a brake pad inspection to determine the extent of the wear. A mechanic can check the brake pads and rotors to see if they're within the recommended wear limits. \n\nYou can also try to tighten the caliper bolts to see if that resolves the issue, but be careful not to over-tighten them, as this can",
